Attribute.name: material
Attribute.title: Material of the Lateral Load-Resisting System

AtomsGroup.name: height_ground_floor
AtomsGroup.title: Height of ground floor above grade

Atom.name: MDD
Atom.title: Different materials in the two directions

Atom.name: CLBLH
Atom.title: Fired clay hollow blocks or tiles

Atom.name: LDD
Atom.title: Different types of llrs in the two directions

Atom.name: LFLSINF
Atom.title: Infilled flat slab/plate or infilled waffle slab

Atom.name: LHV
Atom.title:
LHV(sys_a-sys_b), hybrid LLRS in height 
(a= primary system and secondary system)

Atom.name: LFC
Atom.title: Lateral load coefficient
Atom.desc: LFC:n, n is the lateral force coefficient in percentage (%)

Atom.name: DBD
Atom.title: Equipped with base isolation and/or energy dissipation devices

Atom.name: DCW
Atom.title: Columns-Wall density
Atom.desc: Float specifying the density or ratio between the area of columns and/or walls and the area of the building plan.

Atom.name: H
Atom.title: Number of storeys above ground
Atom.desc:
H:n, exact number of storeys above ground.
H:a-b, range of storeys above ground.
H:<n, n upper limit of number of storeys above ground (with n excluded).
H:>n, n lower limit of number of storeys above ground (with n excluded).

Atom.name: HAPP
Atom.title: Approximate number of storeys above ground

Atom.name: HHT
Atom.title: Total height of the structure, measured from the ground floor.
Atom.desc:
Total height of the structure, measured from the ground floor. Float specifying the height of the structures in meters. (HHT>= 1)
HHT:n

Atom.name: HHI
Atom.title: Inter-storey height (average)
Atom.desc:
Float specifying the average floor height in meters. (HHI>= 1)
HHI:n

Atom.name: HB
Atom.title: Number of storeys below ground
Atom.desc:
Number of storeys below ground (same as number of basements).
HB:n, exact number of storeys below ground.
HB:a-b, range of storeys below ground.
HB:<n, n upper limit of number of storeys below ground (with n excluded).
HB:>n, n lower limit of number of storeys below ground (with n excluded).

Atom.name: HBAPP
Atom.title: Approximate number of storeys below ground

Atom.name: HF
Atom.title: Height of ground floor level above grade
Atom.desc:
HF:n, exact height of ground floor above grade.
HF:a-b, range of height of ground floor above grade.
HF:<n, n upper limit of the height of ground floor above grade. (with n excluded).
HF:>n, n lower limit of the height of ground floor above grade. (with n excluded).

Atom.name: HFAPP
Atom.title: Approximate height of ground floor level above grade

Atom.name: HD
Atom.title: Slope of the ground
Atom.desc:
Slope of the ground (n=float in degrees).
HD:n

Atom.name: Y
Atom.title: Date of construction or retrofit
Atom.desc:
Y:n, exact date of construction or retrofit.
Y:a-b, range of date of construction or retrofit.
Y:<n, n upper limit of date of construction or retrofit (with n excluded).
Y:>n, n lower limit of date of construction or retrofit (with n excluded).

Atom.name: YAPP
Atom.title: Approximate date of construction or retrofit

Atom.name: PLFSQO
Atom.title: Square, with an interior opening (e.g. a "donut")

Atom.name: CHV
Atom.title: Change in vertical structure (includes large overhangs)

Atom.name: GFO
Atom.title: Ground floor plan fully open (no walls)

Atom.name: GFH
Atom.title: Ground floor plan partially open (i.e. with at least 50% of walls).

Atom.name: WOL
Atom.title: Large openings (i.e. more than 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: WOM
Atom.title: Moderate openings (i.e. from 20% to 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: WOS
Atom.title: Small openings (i.e. less than 20% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: RWCP
Atom.title: Roof-wall diaphragm connection present (the connection  transfers in-plane forces from floor to wall and restrains wall outward displacements)

Atom.name: RTDP
Atom.title: Roof tie-down present (a connection that provides vertical attachment of roof to wall in order to restrain roof from upward displacement, lift-off due to wind)

Atom.name: FN
Atom.title: No elevated or suspended floor material (single-storey building)

Atom.name: FM3
Atom.title: Composite cast-in-place reinforced concrete and masonry floor system

Atom.name: FC3
Atom.title: Precast concrete floor with reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: FC4
Atom.title: Precast concrete floor without reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: FME1
Atom.title: Metal beams, trusses, or joists supporting light flooring

Atom.name: FME2
Atom.title: Metal beams supporting precast concrete slabs

Atom.name: FME3
Atom.title: Composite steel deck and concrete slab

Atom.name: FW1
Atom.title: Wooden beams or trusses and joists supporting light flooring

Atom.name: FW2
Atom.title: Wooden beams or trusses and joists supporting heavy flooring

Atom.name: FW3
Atom.title: Wood-based sheets on joists or beams

Atom.name: FW4
Atom.title: Plywood panels or other light-weight panels for floor

Atom.name: FWCP
Atom.title: Floor-wall diaphragm connection present (the role of the connection is to restrain wall out-of-plane forces and to transfer in-plane forces to wall)

RM.title: Composite masonry and concrete roof system

RC.title: Precast concrete roof with reinforced concrete topping
Precast concrete roof without reinforced concrete topping

RME.title: Metal or steel beams or trusses supporting light roofing
Metal or steel beams supporting precast concrete slabs
Composite steel deck and concrete slab

RWO.title: Wooden structure with light roof covering
Wooden beams or trusses with  heavy roof covering
Wood-based sheets on rafters or purlins
Plywood panels or other light-weight panels for roof
